{"sequence":19,"timestamp":"2026-04-15T05:32:08.548881212Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-1-50cb47ee","body":"finding_summary: The newly added benchmark instructions for `ralph-burning-juj` will not run the release profile as written. The command places `--release` after `--`, so Cargo forwards it to the test binary instead of enabling release-mode compilation, which invalidates the bead's step-1 hypothesis check.\nseverity: medium\naffected_files:\n- .beads/issues.jsonl\nevidence:\n- .beads/issues.jsonl:117 embeds `cargo test --locked --features test-stub --test cli cli_run_start_releases_lock_on_error -- --exact --release`.\n- `cargo test --help` documents `--release` as a Cargo compilation option that must appear before the `-- [ARGS]...` separator.\nremediation_hint: Move `--release` into Cargo's option section, for example `cargo test --release --locked --features test-stub --test cli cli_run_start_releases_lock_on_error -- --exact`, and make the same fix anywhere else this measurement command is copied.","dedup_key":"e3c17fed62091f921baeb3812b73c81f13904b10ee85afa2f6f8667fbee7b50c","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"codex","model_id":"gpt-5.4-xhigh","reviewer_id":"reviewer-1"}],"run_id":"run-20260415043544","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
{"sequence":20,"timestamp":"2026-04-15T05:32:08.555445730Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-1-9570b4ae","body":"The acceptance criteria specify 'Target: single CLI lifecycle test under 15 seconds (currently 67-85s)' and 'Measurable reduction in stub-backend test execution time'. Neither criterion is met. While the hypothesis was correctly tested and disproven (release mode yields ~6% improvement on the single test but the full suite and conformance are actually slower), the performance problem persists at 69.65s — 4.6x over the 15s target. A new bead should investigate the actual bottleneck. The release-vs-debug data strongly suggests the overhead is not CPU-bound (compiler optimizations don't help), so the root cause is likely: (1) excessive sleep/timeout durations in stub backends, (2) subprocess spawning overhead, or (3) synchronization/polling intervals in the test harness. Profiling with strace/perf to identify the dominant wait source would be the right next step.","dedup_key":"35907a6ab78da1c7e6c10ee2a986dfc8ed1d78a18aacda9eef35b0afb5f0dc83","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"claude","model_id":"claude-opus-4-6-max","reviewer_id":"reviewer-2"}],"run_id":"run-20260415043544","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
